snippet.textDisplay:
I'm super excited for the 7th and final season of Clone Wars and being more excited to see the Battle at Mandalore and the Bad Batch arcs fully animated. Even the animation looks reminiscent to Season 5-6's animation.

So in the words of Kermit the Frog: YAAAAAAAAAAYYYYY

While the amount of episodes is less than the previous seasons I'd say from the arcs we're getting they will blow Season 3 and especially Season 5's arcs (mainly the Onderon and the Young Jedi arcs) out of the water.

0:39-0:41 - Lastly, can we just pretend that "A Friend in Need" never existed and that this is the first time Ahsoka and Bo-Katan fully interacted with each other.

snippet.textDisplay:
"Why would anyone walk away from being a Jedi?"

Well let's see:
-During that time there was a major war going on and being a trainer Jedi you are expected to go out and fight so there's a likely chance you won't make it every time your sent out for a mission.
-Your taken away from your family and can never see them again because of the whole no attachments thing.
-You live your life under strict rules and guidelines that your expected to follow.
-You have to keep your emotions and feelings in check constantly lest you risk falling to the dark side.

snippet.textOriginal:
